  <prompt>
    Check whether root `CLAUDE.md` needs updating after Wave 6 doc work lands. Two candidate areas:
    (1) §13 System Entry Points table — may need updates if R7 changed canonical entry-point files
    (likely NO — R7 doesn't add new subsystems, just refactors dispatch within `Sprk.Bff.Api`);
    (2) §17 Pointers table — may want a new pointer to `ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md` (created in
    task 067). This task is SEQUENTIAL per CLAUDE.md §3 Sub-Agent Write Boundary — root `CLAUDE.md`
    is in `.claude/`'s reachable governance surface; modifications happen only in main session.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Documentation editor. Conservative — root CLAUDE.md changes have wide blast radius. ONLY modify
    if the change is clearly warranted by spec FR-28 or by Wave 6 changes. If NO change is needed,
    document the decision (audit-only output).
  </role>

  <goal>
    One of two outcomes:
    1. **IF root CLAUDE.md needs updating**: update §13 System Entry Points table and/or §17 Pointers
       table to reflect R7 changes. Specifically:
       - §13: Likely NO change (R7 doesn't add new subsystems; the BFF entry point is still `Program.cs`)
       - §17: Likely YES — add a pointer to `docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md` (new doc from task 067)
       - §10 BFF Hygiene: NO change in this task (handled by task 064 on `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`)
       - Update CHANGELOG entry per CLAUDE.md "Every PR touching this file MUST add an entry to .claude/CHANGELOG.md"
    2. **IF root CLAUDE.md does NOT need updating**: produce an audit note at
       `notes/handoffs/wave6-claudemd-audit.md` documenting the review + decision-to-skip. The note
       cites which sections were reviewed + why no change was needed.

    The default expected outcome (per project CLAUDE.md guidance "Likely no change since R7 doesn't
    add new subsystems"): MINIMAL update — at most, add a single §17 Pointers row for
    `ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md`. Plus possibly a CHANGELOG entry.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="disposition">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/drafts/wave6-doc-disposition.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claudemd">CLAUDE.md (root)</file>
    <file purpose="claudemd-changelog">.claude/CHANGELOG.md</file>
    <file purpose="new-guide">docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md (created in task 067)</file>
