      <item>Task 069 post-audits docs/ for SUPERSEDED markers — root CLAUDE.md is reviewed there too.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: docs UPDATE task to root CLAUDE.md (Sub-Agent Write Boundary applies — main session only) — sequential per CLAUDE.md §3 · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-28 + task 060 disposition list + root CLAUDE.md §13 + §17 + §10.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Determine §13 System Entry Points disposition">
      Review §13 table. R7 doesn't add new subsystems (no new BFF API, no new PCF, no new code page). Likely NO change. Document the audit decision.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Determine §17 Pointers disposition">
      Review §17 table. R7 creates `docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md` (task 067). Determine whether §17 should add a pointer to this guide. Likely YES — but as a single new row, not a refactor of the table.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Determine §10 BFF Hygiene disposition">
      Confirm §10 already cites `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` — task 064 updated §G within that file, not the citation from root CLAUDE.md. No change needed in §10 in this task.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Branch on outcome">
      IF any change is needed (Step 3 likely yields YES): proceed to Step 6 (Apply update).
      IF no change is needed: proceed to Step 7 (Audit-only output).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Apply update (if needed)">
      Add a row to §17 Pointers table. Suggested row:
      | Topic | Pointer |
      |---|---|
      | **Wiring a new consumer (maker tutorial)** | [`docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md`](docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md) — what a consumer is, step-by-step wiring procedure, chat-summarize migration case study (R7 FR-31) |
      Place alphabetically or near "Module-specific CLAUDE.md" / similar pointer entries.

      ALSO update `.claude/CHANGELOG.md`: add a single line entry citing this task + the §17 addition.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Audit-only output (if no change)">
      Create `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/handoffs/wave6-claudemd-audit.md` with:
      - Date + author
      - Review summary (§13 / §17 / §10 checked)
      - Decision: no change needed + rationale per section
      - Next-action: none (Wave 6 task 069 post-audits independently)
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify Sub-Agent Write Boundary respected">
      Confirm this task ran in main session (no sub-agent tool calls modifying root CLAUDE.md or `.claude/CHANGELOG.md`).
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify NFR-08 discipline">
      Grep any modified file for "SUPERSEDED" / "deprecated" added during this task. Zero new instances.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 068 status complete; advance current-task.md to next pending Wave 6 task (069).
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit any modified files with conventional message.
      Example (update path): docs(claudemd/r7): add §17 pointer to ai-guide-consumer-wiring (Wave 6 task 068, FR-28)
      Example (audit-only path): docs(audit/r7): root CLAUDE.md no-change audit (Wave 6 task 068, FR-28)
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (root CLAUDE.md + CHANGELOG + new guide + spec)</tool>
    <tool>Grep (verify cross-references + NFR-08 markers)</tool>
    <tool>Edit (root CLAUDE.md + .claude/CHANGELOG.md, if needed)</tool>
